[SN]TITLE[SN]
County Championship: Glamorgan v Derbyshire (Sun)

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Andrew Salter and Owen Morgan could play for Glamorgan as the Welsh county and Derbyshire aim for their first County Championship win this season.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Glamorgan have named the young spinners in their squad but batsmen Chris Cooke and Colin Ingram and bowlers Dean Cosker and Timm van der Gugten are out.
Derbyshire's Harvey Hosein will play his first Championship game this year for regular wicketkeeper Tom Poynton.
Will Davis returns for Derbyshire but fellow bowler Tom Taylor (back) is out.
Glamorgan (from): Selman, Wallace, Bragg, Rudolph (c), Donald, Lloyd, Wagg, Meschede, Salter, Morgan, Hogan, Murphy.
Derbyshire (from): Godleman, Rutherford, C Hughes, Madsen, Broom, Slater, Thakor, Hemmings, Critchley, Hosein, Palladino, Davis, Cotton.
